Each castle that is constructed that does not directly grant a title does advance the player within the levels for that title. Each castle is worth four levels; for example, building a fifth castled city will grant a Duke level 4 within his title rank. This advancement is only for the purpose of determining how many Barons can be created, and thus how many cities may be held.

